---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'

export const prerender = true
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Changelog"
  description="New ilo research, drafting, scheduling, and publishing features."
>
  <main class="site-frame py-16">
    <article class="content-prose">
      <h1>Changelog</h1>
      <p>What changed in the CLI, local MCP server, TypeScript package, and public site.</p>

      <h2>July 16, 2026</h2>
      <h3>Publish through Typefully and switch between X accounts</h3>
      <p>
        ilo can now connect a personal Typefully v2 API key or several direct X
        OAuth accounts. Every draft keeps its original X handle and publishing
        provider, even after the local default changes.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Typefully setup imports every accessible social set with an X profile.</li>
        <li>Account aliases work across the CLI, local MCP server, and TypeScript package.</li>
        <li>Top-level posts, replies, static images, and local schedules use the selected provider.</li>
        <li>Research still uses public FxTwitter data and local SQLite.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        The <a href="/docs/accounts">publishing accounts guide</a> covers setup,
        account switching, draft binding, media limits, and credential storage.
      </p>

      <h3>Search the people an X account follows</h3>
      <p>
        Following sync now saves complete available public profiles instead of
        relationship IDs alone. Search names, handles, bios, locations, and
        aliases locally, export every match to CSV, or inspect one complete
        stored profile.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Resumable syncs refresh completed snapshots automatically.</li>
        <li>Coverage includes completion, profile counts, errors, age, and 24-hour freshness.</li>
        <li>CLI and MCP search return every match unless you set a limit.</li>
        <li>The public TypeScript package exposes the same sync, status, search, and profile functions.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        The <a href="/docs/following-search">following search guide</a> has the
        complete CLI, MCP, TypeScript, JSON, CSV, refresh, and evidence workflow.
      </p>
    </article>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
